Is there something that needs to be done in Cloudflare, or might it just take a bit longer?

Michael

Hi Michael,

All good, in response to your questions:

  1. So I can change the Cloudflare name servers at any time, and restore the default name servers from batnorc, without impacting/crashing the site.
***Yes, this is correct, you will have to make sure the domain records are intact through. Perhaps Fundraisin can help you with this?

  1. Doing so would enable the zone manager / DNS settings within batnorc, so I have access for when I am ready to move the website.
***Yes, this is also correct.

  1. Then when I am ready to migrate the site, I can update the DNS settings (CNAME and A records) to point the site to the Funraisin servers.
*** This is also correct.

  1. I can then let you know to shut down the WordPress site and cancel hosting, etc.
***Yes, this is correct also.

For the DNS updates etc., it might be best for you to work with your IT provider, that may be batnorc? I'm not sure. It's something that's simple to do, once you know the intricate details of it all, if that makes sense.

Thanks Heath

Sorry for all the questions, this stuff is a little outside my skillset.


  1. So I can change the Cloudflare name servers at any time, and restore the default name servers from batnorc, without impacting/crashing the site.




  1. Doing so would enable the zone manager / DNS settings within batnorc, so I have access for when I am ready to move the website.




  1. Then when I am ready to migrate the site, I can update the DNS settings (CNAME and A records) to point the site to the Funraisin servers.




  1. I can then let you know to shut down the WordPress site and cancel hosting, etc.



Have I understood this all correctly?

MK

Michael Klinakis​

Website and Platforms Manager

Hi Michael,

No there won't be any downtime during the change over. 🙂

Thanks Heath

Does that mean the website will be down for a period of time, after the name servers are changed and until the new DNS settings propagate?

MK

Michael Klinakis​

Website and Platforms Manager

t:
03 98452887

Hi Michael,

Yes that's correct, the domain is managed in CloudFlare. It's actually within the MS Australia's account still, so the best course of action will likely be to mange it from within your domain portal. You would just need to remove the CloudFlare Name Servers, and use those of your domain portal or preferred domain host.

Does that make sense? I'm happy to help out if need be.

full_threads.body:

I am getting ready to move the kissgoodbyetoms.org website onto the Funraisin platform, and was wondering how I would go about updating DNS settings (when I'm ready to move it) as from what I can see, it is currently connected to Cloudflare so I can't see/access zone manager in our domain portal?


Kind Regards
Michael
